<paragraph id="8B9536CD812BF430FF0675F64DD9488F" blockId="9.[136,1452,1993,2093]" lastBlockId="10.[136,1451,158,400]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="9" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812BF433FF0675F64C7E4FB7" bold="true" box="[136,349,1993,2020]" pageId="9" pageNumber="27">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E812BF433FEF775F54F0C4FB7" authorityName="Holub" authorityYear="1973" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[377,559,1994,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pichleri">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812BF433FEF775F54F0C4FB7" box="[377,559,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="27">Cyanus pichleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by two subspecies in 
<collectingCountry id="F33D765D812BF433FC6F75F549124FB7" box="[993,1073,1994,2020]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="27">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B3C812BF433FBCD75F549D04FB6" author="Wagenitz, G." box="[1091,1267,1994,2021]" pageId="9" pageNumber="27" pagination="465 - 585" refId="ref20808" refString="Wagenitz, G. (1975) Centaurea L. In: Davis, P. H. (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands, vol. 5. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, pp. 465 - 585." type="book chapter" year="1975">Wagenitz 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B3C812BF433FA8C75F548BC4FB7" author="Greuter, W." box="[1282,1439,1994,2020]" pageId="9" pageNumber="27" pagination="49 - 61" refId="ref17790" refString="Greuter, W. (2003) The Euro + Med treatment of Cardueae (Compositae) - generic concepts and required new names. Willdenowia 33: 49 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.3372 / wi. 33.33104" type="journal article" year="2003">Greuter 2003</bibRefCitation>
): subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E812BF433FE8975D14C7D405B" authorityName="Holub" authorityYear="1973" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[263,350,2030,2056]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pichleri">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812BF433FE8975D14C7D405B" box="[263,350,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="27">pichleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has involucers in 15–20 × (8–)9–13(–15) mm size, cilia in (l.5–) 
<quantity id="4CD29B28812BF433FBBC75D149B2405B" box="[1074,1169,2030,2057]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
length, peripheral florets strongly radiant and ca. 
<quantity id="4CD29B28812BF433FE147A2D4F37407F" box="[410,532,2066,2093]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="15.0">15–20 mm</quantity>
longer than the involucre; and subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E812BF433FC777A2D49B4407F" box="[1017,1175,2066,2092]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="extrarosularis">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF812BF433FC777A2D49B4407F" box="[1017,1175,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="27">extrarosularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has involucres in 11–15 × 7–8(–9) mm size, cilia in 1–1.5(–2) mm length, peripheral florets slightly radiant and ca. 
<quantity id="4CD29B288128F430FB2872A149D448EA" box="[1190,1271,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
longer than the involucre.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536CD8128F430FF3372D94886491A" blockId="10.[136,1451,158,400]" pageId="10" pageNumber="28">
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4B3C8128F430FF3372D94CB24953" author="Bornmuller, J." box="[189,401,230,256]" pageId="10" pageNumber="28" pagination="309 - 420" refId="ref17142" refString="Bornmuller, J. (1944) Symbolae ad Floram Anatolicam. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 89: 309 - 420." type="journal article" year="1944">Bornmüller (1944)</bibRefCitation>
described his new variety (i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8128F430FD7A72D84EBE4953" box="[756,925,231,257]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="pichleri" variety="ancyrensis">
var. 
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8128F430FCA872D84EBE4953" box="[806,925,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="28">ancyrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) on the basis of lyrate basal leaves of the 
<typeStatus id="5491886F8128F430FAF572D848884952" box="[1403,1451,231,257]" pageId="10" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
specimen. My extensive examinations of specimens at different herbaria revealed the presence of a continuous range of the basal leaves from undivided to lyrate. Therefore this 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8128F430FCAE73114EE3491B" box="[800,960,302,328]" pageId="10" pageNumber="28" rank="variety" variety="should">variety should</taxonomicName>
be considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D4E8128F430FAA8731048BD491B" authorityName="Holub" authorityYear="1973" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[1318,1438,302,329]" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pichleri">
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8128F430FAA87310481A491A" box="[1318,1337,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="28">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95EEADF8128F430FAC9731148BD491B" box="[1351,1438,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="28">pichleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
